```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.facebookusercollecti">

    <!-- 
    Problem: In modern social media management, users often struggle with the need for consistent and timely engagement on platforms like Facebook.
    Solution: This Android application serves as a social media management tool, facilitating automation for ongoing operations.
    -->

    <!-- Required permissions to access the internet and network state for continuous operation -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    <!-- 
    Problem: Without internet permissions, the application cannot communicate with social media platforms.
    This permission solves the problem of ensuring that the app can send and receive data as needed for automation.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />
    <!-- 
    Problem: Monitoring network state is essential for optimizing resource use and ensuring reliable operations.
    This permission addresses the challenge of keeping track of network availability for effective scheduling of automated tasks.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <!-- 
    Problem: Users may want to save logs or other data generated by the application to the device.
    This permission allows the app to store necessary files, overcoming the limitation of data storage.
    -->

    <!-- Application declaration -->
    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="@string/app_name"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/Theme.AppCompat.Light.NoActionBar">
        
        <!-- 
        Main Activity Declaration
        Problem: Users require a user-friendly interface to configure and manage their social media automation settings.
        The MainActivity serves as the entry point for users, allowing them to easily navigate through the application settings.
        -->
        <activity
            android:name=".MainActivity"
            android:exported="true">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
        Automation Service Declaration
        Problem: Automation tasks need to run continuously in the background without user interaction.
        The AutomationService ensures that the management tasks operate seamlessly 24/7, addressing the need for consistent engagement on social media platforms.
        -->
        <service
            android:name=".AutomationService"
            android:exported="false">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="com.madhub.facebookusercollecti.ACTION_AUTOMATE" />
            </intent-filter>
        </service>

    </application>
</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Key Components:
- **Permissions**: The defined permissions ensure that the application can operate effectively in terms of network access and data storage, directly addressing common issues faced by social media management tools.
- **MainActivity**: This component serves as the primary interface for users, facilitating ease of use in managing automation settings.
- **AutomationService**: This service allows for continuous background operations, ensuring that users can maintain consistent engagement without manual intervention. This aligns with MadHub's technical characteristics of providing 24/7 automated operations on the Android platform.
